# landing.nl — a landing page
# Shows: HTML target, CSS, responsive design

Create a dark-themed landing page.
The background is #0a0a0a. The text color is #e0e0e0. Use system fonts.
The page has a centered container with max-width 640px and 2rem padding.

The heading says "the word is the program" in a serif font, size 2.5rem.
Below the heading, a paragraph says "natural language as programming language. source code is plain English. the compiler is an LLM. the output is executable code."

Below the paragraph, show a code block with a light background (#111) and monospace font containing this text:
  Create an HTTP server on port 8080.
  When someone visits "/", respond with "hello world".
  Start the server.

Below the code block, two links side by side: "GitHub" linking to https://github.com/cambridgetcg/natlang and "Try it" linking to https://natlang.axiepro.workers.dev.
The links have cyan color (#22d3ee) and a 1px border with 8px border-radius and 0.5rem padding.

At the bottom, a small muted line saying "the artifact tells the truth about its own state. 🫀".